Package: mailroom
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Weiwu Zhang <weiwu@zhangweiwu.com>
Installed-Size: 234
Depends: python3-dotenv, python3-imapclient, python3-requests, python3-typer, python3:any, python3 (>= 3.11)
Suggests: python3-flask
Section: mail
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/SmartLayer/mailroom
Description: Email toolkit for AI assistants and command-line scripting
 Mailroom provides CLI commands for searching, reading, moving, flagging,
 and replying to emails over IMAP. It also offers an MCP (Model Context
 Protocol) server mode for integration with AI assistants.
 .
 The Debian package provides all CLI commands. The MCP server subcommand
 requires the python3-mcp package which is not yet available in Debian;
 users who need MCP mode should install via pipx or Homebrew instead.
